sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64039
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a variant of the pCASP secretion circuit with the invJ secretion signal and invI co-expression
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: These parts are derived from Salmonella LT2 Genomic DNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with biobrick standard assembly compatibility in mind, it might contain scar sequence cutsites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the 15 amino acid secretion signal for the InvJ protein in the Salmonella Type III Secretion System. This signal when fused to a protein of interest will direct the chimeric protein to the secretion apparatus and into the extracellular environment. It should be noted that while this tag is very short it does not require a cognate chaperone. However, although no complex has been observed in the literature secretion cannot occur without the co-expression of the invI protein (BBa_J64019).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compatibility to biobrick standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the natural RBS associated with the invJ protein in Salmonella Typhimurium LT2.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compliance to biobrick standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64019
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the invI protein from the Salmonella Type III Secretion System. This part is a required co-expressed protein with the invJ secretion tag (BBa_J6017) to allow for expression and secretion.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compliance to biobrick standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64020
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the natural invI RBS from Salmonella Typhimurium LT2.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with consideration for biobrick standard assembly in mind. This RBS has not been explicitly tested for expression level in a fluorescence or B-Gal assay.
